Team Introduction
The Engineering Productivity Serverless team is committed to building industry-leading R&D Serverless solutions, including basic runtime, high-density deployment, universal deployment capabilities, commercialization solutions, etc.

What you will be doing:
- Responsible for the end-to-end development of internal tools;
- Building a world-class backend, which combines usability, accessibility, elegance, performance, and maintainability;
- Develop advanced intelligent data platform, and help client developers make decisions to optimize the user experience of our products;
- Improve the reliability of the system, and manage the challenges of scale and complexity;
- Introduce new server architecture, to squeeze extreme performance from hardware and handle large amounts of requests. 

Qualifications

 What you should have:
- Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or related major;
- At least 3 years of industry experience in a software development environment;
- Proficiency in backend-related technologies such as Java/ Golang/ Node.js/ Python/ C++;
- Familiar with commonly used database systems, like MySQL and PostgreSQL;
- Familiar with construction and continuous integration, familiarity with at least one construction tool;
- Familiar with Unix/Linux operating systems;
- Excellent problem-analysis and problem-solving skills, able and willing to seek challenges, and acquire new knowledge.

